.TH VOIX 1 "April 2026" "Voix 2.4.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
voix \- a modern, secure privilege escalation tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B voix
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
[\fICOMMAND\fR [\fIARGS\fR...]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Voix is a secure, modern, and easy-to-use privilege escalation tool for Unix-like operating systems. It is designed to be a secure replacement for \fBsudo\fR and is inspired by \fBOpenDoas\fR. Voix uses Pluggable Authentication Modules (PAM) for authentication and has a simple, easy-to-understand configuration file.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-u, \-\-user \fIUSER\fR
Execute command as the specified user (default: root).
.TP
.B \-C, \-\-clear
Clear any persisted authentications for the current user.
.TP
.B \-n, \-\-non-interactive
Fail if a password is required, rather than prompting.
.SH CONFIGURATION
The Voix configuration file, located at \fI/etc/voix.conf\fR, defines the rules for command execution.
.PP
The syntax is as follows:
.PP
.B [permit|deny] [persist] <identity> [as <target>] [cmd <command> [args ...]]
.PP
.TP
.B permit
Allow the user to execute a command.
.TP
.B deny
Prevent the user from executing any command.
.TP
.B persist
The user will not be prompted for a password.
.TP
.B as
The user to execute the command as (defaults to root).
.TP
.B cmd
The command to be executed. If no command is specified, any command is allowed.
.SH AUTHENTICATION
Voix uses the Pluggable Authentication Modules (PAM) framework for authentication.
The service name is \fBvoix\fR, and its configuration can be found in \fI/etc/pam.d/voix\fR.
.PP
A typical configuration is as follows:
.IP
.nf
#%PAM-1.0
auth       include      system-auth
account    include      system-auth
password   include      system-auth
session    include      system-auth
.fi
.SH EXAMPLES
Execute \fBwhoami\fR as root:
.IP
voix whoami
.PP
Execute \fBwhoami\fR as a specific user:
.IP
voix -u user whoami
.PP
Restart a service:
.IP
voix /usr/bin/systemctl restart nginx.service
.PP
Allow a user to run a specific command without a password:
.IP
.nf
# /etc/voix.conf
permit persist :wheel
.fi
